3. Process Hazard Analysis ? A detailed process hazard assessment, using HAZOP, is conducted on the facility to insure that it has been designed safely. PAS-04 Process Hazard Analysis Procedure and associated job aids include a description of how the Process Hazard Analysis element is implemented.; 

4. Operating Procedures ? A system is in place to ensure that updated and approved procedures cover the facility's operation. PAS-64 Operating Procedures includes a description of how the Operating Procedure element is implemented; 

5. Training ? A training program has been established to ensure that personnel are well trained in the specific duties of their jobs (The process also includes an annual Training Needs Analysis). The training department is responsible for training of operations personnel. ; 

6. Contractors ? It is FHR's objective to partner with contractors that share the same safety philosophy. A dedicated, collective, and consistent approach by FHR and contractors will enhance and maintain the safety and health of our respective employees. The PSM Contractor Management Program element is included in R-01 Contractor EHS Procedure; 

7. Prestart up Safety Review ? A prestart up safety review walk down and checklist is completed for changes that impact the Process Safety Information. PAS-72.01Procedure

