Process ID: 74829 - LIGHT OLEFINS UNIT (LOU)



The Light Olefins Unit (LOU) Process has five units which are the Hot Side, Cold Side, GHU, PDU and LOU Offsites. The Hot Side includes the furnaces up through the quench columns. The Cold Side includes compression, refrigeration, and fractionation. GHU is a two stage gasoline hydrogenation unit. The PDU is the propylene drying and transfer unit. LOU Offsites include tankage, waste water stripping unit, flare, custody transfer stations, and loading racks associated with the LOU. The process controls, mitigations, monitors and detectors listed apply to all units except as follows: the PDU and LOU Offsites do not have automatic shutoffs; the GHU and Cold Side are the only units with quench system process controls; only LOU Offsite unit tankage have dikes; the GHU does not have process area detectors; and fire detectors are only at the PDU, LOU, Compressor Decks, and LOU Lube Oil Skids. The flammable mixture mass noted below includes inventories of non RMP flammable chemicals and RMP flammable chemicals below the threshold quantity in the process. RMP chemicals below the threshold quantity included in the flammable mixture are: Acetylene, Ethyl Acetylene, cylohexlamine, Vinyl acetate, Hydrogen Sulfide, Carbon Disulfide, Methyl Mercaptan, Ethyl Mercaptan, Formaldehyde and Hydrogen.



